SIMPLE: irresoluble
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Irresoluble
<hw>Ir*res"o*lu*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>irresolubilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>irr⟦eacute⟧soluble</ets>. See
<er>Resoluble</er>, and cf. <er>Irresolvable</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Incapable of being dissolved or resolved into parts;
insoluble.</def> <rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Incapable of being relieved or assisted.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The second is in the <qex>irresoluble</qex> condition of our souls
after a known sin committed.</q> <rj><qau>Bp. Hall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Irresolubleness</ent>⟦br⟧
